    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>POI should have a cell.getRawValueAsString() method, but AFAIK that's not the case. The displayed text you see in excel is the sum of value + format. So if you want to recover it \"as displayed\":</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Retrieve cell value from cell object</li>\n<li>Retrieve cell format using associated CellStyle.</li>\n<li>apply format to value using DataFormatter</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3309393,
      "reputation" : 8627,
      "user_id" : 2783244,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/V4exP.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "StoopidDonut",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2783244/stoopiddonut"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1760091826,
    "last_edit_date" : 1760091826,
    "creation_date" : 1394103535,
    "answer_id" : 22222425,
    "question_id" : 22221700,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Change:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>System.out.println(resultRow.getCell(0));\n</code></pre>\n<p>To:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>System.out.println(new DataFormatter().formatCellValue(resultRow.getCell(0)));\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n<p>Apache POI provides for <a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/ibM5W.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>DataFormatter</code></a> class as utility to leverage the format of the content <em>as it appears</em> in Excel. You can choose custom formats too, a simple example would be (cell is reference to your <code>XSSFCell</code> object):</p>\n<p><strong>Excel sheet looks like:</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/ibM5W.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Code:</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>System.out.println(new DataFormatter().formatCellValue(cell));\n</code></pre>\n<p>The above line would print:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>50%\n$ 1,200\n12/21/14\n9886605446\n</code></pre>\n<p>Whereas your normal print would interpret it differently:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>0.5\n1200.0\n21-Dec-2014\n9.886605446E9\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
